It’s been a year since I filmed my music video for “Just A Bordertown” in my hometown of El Paso, TX. It was such a beautiful experience. Thank you to everyone streaming & supporting the song! I love you all so much! With utmost brokenness I feel the need to post about this. I’ve been truly suffering in silence for months. I didn’t want or ask for any of this but in life you have darkness thrown at you and you have no choice but to face it. I’ve had a small army of friends & family fiercely supporting me with the main one being my hero of a husband Mike. He immediately believed me, asked me what I wanted to do and stepped in and spoke on my behalf to call out the behavior. The second I received these texts I was paralyzed and frozen but he aggressively rejected every aspect of the fear, shaming & silencing tactics they both tried to use against me. And on a rainy day in Nashville he walked into a sexual assault center with me. With nervousness and tears I sat there with him, a kind man from Tennessee who worked at the center and we called Nashville Metro to report my assault. The police officer came to the center and treated me with dignity and took my situation seriously. He said he was sorry I was going through this. It took so much love, support, belief in victims for me to survive this trauma. I’m still in it but I know coming forward was an important step for me. My truth is that I tried to handle this civilly and carefully with dignity but was met with threats, fear, blame and humiliation and that wasn’t right. Since December 16 my power was slowly being taken away from me by this person, I was revictimized when I tried to stop it and now I’m making a broken and painful attempt at taking my power back. Through love, prayer, trust and hope I know I’ll come out the other side. I’ve never loved Val more than I do now and that’s something cause I haven’t always loved her and had this much grace and forgiveness for her. So I will take that with me from this. Somehow I feel profound gratitude through this violent storm. I’m sorry for any victim who’s suffered through this alone. I’m sending you the most love belief dignity and grace today ❤️‍🩹 #trauma #healing

I recorded this on April 4, 2023. I was recording a “Get Ready w/ Me” vid. I had kept quiet about my assault in December 2022. I had tweeted something earlier in this day in April vaguely alluding that something bad had happened to me & was going through something traumatic. I received a concerned text while recording the video from someone who saw my tweet. Feeling the budding support outside of my close friends & family caught me off guard. I had kept so much inside because of the threats & fear that came from confronting the perpetrator & his fiancé. I live in the same apartment complex as them as well as the friend who ignored me so that has added to the terror I’ve been experiencing. Coming forward was an important step. I want people to understand how predatory & scary these situations can be for victims. For all the people who have surrounded me & believed me it’s made all the difference. From my husband to friends to family to Nashville Metro Police to Music Health Alliance I can’t begin to tell how important it’s been that I felt safe & protected in coming forward. I’m still processing the trauma & fearful but opening up has been a lifeline for me. I hope this can help people understand how important it is to be the for someone when they experience SA & trauma. #healing #trauma
